  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Trucked Water Needed for Cite Solail School, Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fountains of Hope would like to provide 3000 gallons of trucked in water on a weekly basis to a school of 600 children located in the heart of the third largest slum in the world, Cite Solail, Haiti.  Donors would sponsor water that will fill two tanks every week.  There is a water purifier system at the facility which has been previously donated that can purify each tank in 20 minutes making the water potable for the children to use on a daily basis.   52 weeks x $60 per truckload = $3,120</narrative>
  </description>
